	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Expanding MBC2 ROM to 512kb</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The physical MBC2 IC cannot support more than 256 KiB, but beyond that it really depends on just how anal-retentive the programmer for the emulator/PLD was.<br /><br />You should be able to hack it to work on an MBC1+RAM or MBC5+RAM, anyway, since the MBC2 is approximately a subset.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


